description:
Based on the controlled vocabulary of structured data from Schema.org.

In this resume, we used seven main classes from Schema.org: Person, Place, Intangible, Credential, CreativeWork, Event, and Organization, supplemented by secondary classes that extend the properties of these main categories.

Each relevant element of a personal resume — such as the individual, their connections, academic background, professional experience, projects, and other pertinent information — is represented by a specific entity. These entities are laid out in a graph generated by a force-directed algorithm, which maps and reveals the relationships between the various entities described in the resume.
